        <page n="03" image="pa.fr.vs.1870.04.13.03" exists="no">
            <div type="a">
                <column>01</column>
                <head>A Free Lecture</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <transcript>
                    <p/>
                </transcript>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Cathell</ln>
                        <fn>J. Everist</fn>
                        <sf/>
                        <pf/>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>J. Everist Cathell, "The Boy Orator of the Potomac," will deliver a free
                    lecture in the Court House on temperance. "He has travelled all over this
                    country, and through Europe. He is said to be very eloquent and, we doubt not,
                    will have a large audience."</summary>
                <note/>
                <look/>
